		<div id="welcome">

			<h4>*ABOUT STAGE 1</h4>
			Each or any of the <i>Terms, Concept or Specific Objects</i>[words] presented in Stage 1 may invoke personal feelings, spark a particular philosophical interest, connect with you on spiritual level, all three or none at all. Based on your understanding of the words, it’s up to you to reflect on your life’s experience and make selections using our custom graphic interface. (Don't feel you have to select every category for every word)<a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="UI Example"> See Example</a>
			<br /><br />
			<img src="img/s1Img.jpg" style="float:left; margin:0 20px 15px 0;"/>
			<div>
				<strong>Select up to four categories for any given word</strong><br />
				<ul class="about">
					<li>Man's View of Himself (Himself/Herself)</li>
					<li>Man's Connections with Other than Himself</li>
					<li>Man's View of the World</li>
					<li>Man's Physical Activities</li>
				</ul>
				<strong>The word "Man" means the <i>universal man</i> of which you are an example. <br />As such, you may consider:</strong><br />
            	<ul class="about">
					<li><a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Personalize">Personalizing some or all words to yourself</a></li>
					<li><a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Others Exclusively">Thinking of others exclusively</a></li>
					<li><a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Yourself and Others">Thinking of yourself and others together</a></li>
            	</ul>
				<strong>Opinion</strong><br />
			<ul class="about">
				<li><a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Spiritual">Spiritual</a> -- incorruptible | intangible | genuine | essential</li>
				<li><a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Material">Material</a> -- can be sensed or detected | is composed of non-essential parts | can be degraded</li>
				<li><a style="font-weight:700;" href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#definition" data-whatever="Material Spiritual Converging">Spiritual & Material Converging</a> -- unified in a way where, together, it's more than its seperate parts.</li>
				<!--Hypothetical 4: You eat <strong>bread</strong> all the time but never gave it much thought. One day you read how the invention of <strong>bread</strong> was quintessential in man's ability to thrive today.-->
			</ul>
			
			</div><br />
			
			<div id="howto-msg">Continue on to<a href="https://ybigh.herokuapp.com/n-stage1"> Stage 1</a></div>
		 	
		</div>

  	<!-- definitions Modal -->
  <div class="modal fade" id="definition" role="dialog">
    <div class="modal-dialog"> 
      <!-- Modal content-->
      <div class="modal-content">
        <div class="modal-header">
          <h4 class="modal-title"></h4>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-body">
        </div>
        <div class="modal-footer">
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      
    </div>
  </div>
	<script type="text/javascript" src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.3.1/jquery.min.js"></script>
  	<script type="text/javascript" src="libs/boostrap4/js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>

  	<script type="text/javascript">

  	let content = {
  		Material_Spiritual_Converging: "The spiritual realm adds depth and meaning to the material object while the "+ "material object allows expression of the spiritual realm by being its conduit or physical embodiment. A material-spiritual convergence is greater than its individual separate parts.<br /><br /> Like steel reinforcing "+ "concrete. The steel gives flexibility to the concrete and the concrete gives strength to the steel.<br /><br /><strong>Examples of Spiritual & Material Converging</strong>: "+
        "<br />1) You're stranded out at sea and all you have to drink is your own<strong> Urine</strong>. It saves your life."+ 
        "<br />2) You hear about an out-of-control <strong>truck</strong> killing 5 people on a busy <strong>sidewalk</strong>."+
        "<br />3) The <strong>county fair</strong> always held a special place in your heart",
  		Spiritual: "<ul>"+
          	"<li><strong>incorruptible</strong>: beyond reproach or needs no justification -- the meaning of holy text, mathematical shapes, or evil itself, as examples</li>"+
              "<li><strong>intangible</strong>: can't be held or touched. Has no physical presence</li>"+
          	"<li><strong>genuine</strong>: corroborates with what the mind knows it should be and what the thing actually is -- actual gold vs. fools gold</li>"+ 
          	"<li><strong>essential</strong>: complete in a way where it's impossible to think of differently -- Try imagining a square circle if you can</li><br /><strong>Summary:</strong> Things we can feel, believe, or know but not [always] define or understand."+
           "</ul>",
        Material: "<ul>"+
            "<li><strong>can be sensed or detected</strong>: sensed using one or all of the four senses or detected using instruments (microscopes, clocks, etc). Bacteria, birthdays and Broadway plays are some examples</li>"+
          	"<li><strong>composed of non-essential parts</strong>: remove any of its parts and it still exists as that thing -- props and actors are often replaced or removed from a play</li>"+
          	"<li><strong>degradable</strong>: can be ruined or destroyed by a person or over time -- steel on a car eventually corrodes, a copy machine can be crushed using a bat, your 25th birthday wasn't as exciting as your 24th</li>"+
            "<br /><strong>Summary:</strong> Things <i>we</i> create, destroy or discover</ul>",
        UI_Example: "<img src='img/s1Img1.jpg' style='margin:10px;'/>",
        Personalize: "<ul>Example<br /><li><strong>My</strong> View of Myself</li>"+
                     "<li style='color:blue;'><strong>My</strong> Connections with Other than Human (implied)</li>"+
                     "<li><strong>My</strong> View of the World</li>"+
                     "<li><strong>My</strong> Physical Activities</li>"+
                     "<br /><strong>My</strong> -- for a given word you\'re consideing youself, only, for one or more categories.</ul>",
        Others_Exclusively: "<ul>Example (can substitute His/Her as well)<br /><li><strong>Their</strong> View of Themselves</li>"+
                     "<li style='color:blue;'><strong>Their</strong> Connections with Other than Human (implied)</li>"+
                     "<li><strong>Their</strong> View of the World</li>"+
                     "<li><strong>Their</strong> Physical Activities</li>"+
                     "<br /><strong>Their</strong>, <strong>His/Her</strong> -- for a given word you\'re considering other people but not yourself for one or more categories.</ul>",
        Yourself_and_Others: "<ul>Example<br /><li><strong>Our</strong> View of Ourselvse</li>"+
                     "<li style='color:blue;'><strong>Our</strong> Connections with Other than Human (implied)</li>"+
                     "<li><strong>Our</strong> View of the World</li>"+
                     "<li><strong>Our</strong> Physical Activities</li>"+
                     "<br /><strong>Our</strong> -- for a given word you\'re considering either all of mankind, or some subgroup you belong to for one or more categories.</ul>" 
  	}
  		$('#definition').on('show.bs.modal', function (event) {
  			var button = $(event.relatedTarget); // Button that triggered the modal
  			var recipient = button.data('whatever'); // Extract info from data-* attributes
  			var key = recipient.replace(/ /g, "_");
  			var gcontent = content[key];
  			var modal = $(this);
  			modal.find('.modal-title').text(recipient);
  			$('.modal-body').empty();
  			modal.find('.modal-body').append(gcontent);
		})

  	</script>
	</body>
</html>
